724.post_title: PHIATON X TEDDY SPECIAL EDITION HEADPHONES (US ONLY)
724.post_content:
BT460 Model

These special edition headphones are a collaboration between PHIATON and TEDDY, YG’s main in-house producer, who has produced over 100 hit songs. The BBT460 model are wireless headphones that use Bluetooth 4.0 and are equipped with touch interface. The design is available in black and white. Worn by GD & T.O.P in the ‘Zutter’ Music Video and on the Korean variety show Infinity Challenge.

Details: 

Movement Recognition LED Display—a touch panel that allows you to control your music and easily answer and end calls.

Smart Play & Pause—The headphones have a sensor in the ear pads which automatically detects if you are wearing the headphones or have taken them off, and it will play and stop music accordingly.

Multipoint Connection Function—Multipoint connection connects two devices at the same time. You can use any two Bluetooth enabled devices simultaneously, such as your smartphone and tablet PC or your smartphone and MP3 player

PHIATON ShareMe Connection—The headphones allow you to share your entertainment with another person wearing another set of the same headphone featuring Creative ShareMe connectivity.

For Purchase in US ONLY.

Welcome Back is iKON's debut half album. Immediately upon release, the album ranked number three on Billboard's World Albums chart and swooped the number one spot on the iTunes album chart of eleven different territories. The half album features their warm-up single MY TYPE and their two title tracks RHYTHM TA and AIRPLANE. The package includes photobook, CD, and "Welcome Pack" consisting of a sticker set and a random photo card set. 2015, YG Entertainment.
